items.Video_Title: Fake vs Real Converse All Star Chuck Taylor / How to Spot Fake Converse Shoes
items.Video_Description:
Fake vs Real Converse All Star Chuck Taylor

How to spot fake Converse shoes

Original Converse shoes come in a box, if this box is missing, then you are facing a fake Converse.

The price of Converse originals is 80-90 euros, the price of fakes are between 20-40 euros.

Carefully inspect the inner label, the original one must be made in Vietnam, the faakes can be made in China or made in India.

There is a red band in front of the shoe, at the original conversion the space between this band and the end of the shoe (top) is bigger, compared to the fake one which is smaller (see in the video).

Another safety element is the top band that has triangles, compared to the fake one that has vertical stripes. Carefully inspect the end of the tip, it must be clean, without cuts or extra material (see video).

The triangle of white threads under the lace staples, in the original must be smaller, compared to the fake one which is bigger .... see in the video.

The white back stripe above the company logo should be thinner and taller than the fake one which is thicker and smaller ... see in the video.

The front of the convert has a lace-up bag in the middle, the original is higher, thinner and has a different seam at the base (see video), compared to the fake one which is thicker and has a different end seam.

The sole of the original Chuck Taylor All Star Conversion has 5 points at the bottom, compared to the fake one which has only 4 points .... see in the video.
